  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "General Ledger Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Join COSL’s finance team as a General Ledger Accountant, responsible for managing full sets of accounts, preparing reports and forecasts, supporting audits, and ensuring compliance with IFRS, SFRS, and internal policies.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Manage full sets of accounts to ensure accurate financial records and compliance with accounting standards</li><li>Prepare management and statutory reports, forecasts, and reconciliations to support strategic decision-making</li><li>Review divisional reports and accounting entries to maintain data integrity and accuracy</li><li>Oversee the asset register and coordinate audit documentation to facilitate smooth audit processes</li><li>Consolidate financial data from six CNA entities and submit comprehensive monthly reports to the Regional Finance Team</li><li>Coordinate corporate secretary matters with the audit firm to ensure regulatory compliance</li><li>Perform other ad hoc duties to support the finance team’s objectives and operational needs</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accounting or related field</li><li>Minimum 5 years of relevant accounting experience</li><li>Strong knowledge of IFRS and Singapore FRS</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience working in the Oil Rig industry, providing relevant sector-specific accounting expertise</li></ul>",
